---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How Wawasoft and FeedMine handle information."
>
  <section class="pb-14 pt-16 sm:pt-24">
    <p class="font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-wider text-[#8a8a8a]">
      Last updated: July 21, 2026
    </p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-[28px] font-medium leading-tight tracking-tight text-[#1a1a1a] sm:text-[32px]">
      Privacy
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-[620px] text-[16px] leading-relaxed text-[#5c5c5c]">
      Wawasoft builds software that keeps your reading life on your device. This
      policy explains the information practices for FeedMine and this website.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="space-y-10 pb-14">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[16px] font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">FeedMine</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-[620px] text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-[#5c5c5c]">
        FeedMine does not require an account. It does not include advertising,
        analytics, tracking SDKs, or in-app purchases. Wawasoft does not sell,
        rent, or share personal information for advertising.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[16px] font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">Information stored on your device</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-[620px] text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-[#5c5c5c]">
        Your selected sources, reading history, bookmarks, saved searches,
        custom collections, playback state, and app preferences are stored
        locally on your device. FeedMine does not operate a user account system
        or a server that receives this reading data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[16px] font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">Network requests</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-[620px] text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-[#5c5c5c]">
        When you read or refresh a source, FeedMine connects directly to the
        public feed URL or publisher website you chose. Those publishers may
        receive normal network information such as your IP address and browser
        or device details under their own privacy policies. FeedMine also checks
        its public GitHub catalog for available source updates; this check is
        lightweight and does not include your reading history or a user profile.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[16px] font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">Permissions</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-[620px] text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-[#5c5c5c]">
        FeedMine does not collect your location. It may use device storage to
        keep downloaded feed data and local reading state, and it supports
        background audio playback for podcasts.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[16px] font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">This website</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-[620px] text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-[#5c5c5c]">
        This website does not add advertising or analytics trackers. Its hosting
        providers may process standard technical request information needed to
        deliver the site, subject to their own policies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[16px] font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">Contact</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-[620px] text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-[#5c5c5c]">
        Questions about privacy or FeedMine support can be sent to
        <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`} class="font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] underline underline-offset-4 decoration-[#c4bfb4] transition-colors hover:decoration-[#8a8a8a]">
          {site.email}
        </a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
